Digit Reader Example Continued

Read-in the data:

url <- "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/datasciencelabs/data/master/hand-written-digits-train.csv"
digits <- read_csv(url)

Consider only 2s and 7s:

dat <- digits %>% filter(label%in%c(2,7))

Two features

Two predictors

row_column <- expand.grid(row=1:28, col=1:28)
ind1 <- which(row_column$col <= 14 & 
                row_column$row <=14)
ind2 <- which(row_column$col > 14 & 
                row_column$row > 14)
X <- as.matrix(dat[,-1])
X <- X>200
X1 <- rowSums(X[,ind1])/rowSums(X)
X2 <- rowSums(X[,ind2])/rowSums(X)
dat <- mutate(dat, X_1 = X1, X_2 = X2)

Discriminant Analysis

Take a subset and create train and test set:

library(caret)
dat <- sample_n(dat, 1000) %>% 
  select(y, X_1, X_2)
inTrain <- createDataPartition(
  y = dat$y, 
  p = 0.5)$Resample1
train_set <- slice(dat, inTrain)
test_set <- slice(dat, -inTrain)

QDA

Quadratic Discriminant Analysis (QDA) relates to the Naive Bayes

We try to estimate \( \mbox{Pr}(Y=1|X=x) \) using Bayes theorem.

\[ f(x) = \mbox{Pr}(Y=1|\mathbf{X}=\mathbf{x}) = \frac{\pi p_{\mathbf{X}|Y=1}(\mathbf{x})} {(1-\pi) p_{\mathbf{X}|Y=0}(x) + \pi p_{\mathbf{X}|Y=1}(x)} \] Assume \( p \) is normal

Fit the model

We need averages, SDs and correlations: 

params <- train_set %>% group_by(y) %>% 
  summarize(
    avg_1 = mean(X_1),avg_2 = mean(X_2), 
    sd_1= sd(X_1), sd_2 = sd(X_2), 
    r = cor(X_1,X_2))

Problem in Higher Dimensions

With 10 we have 45 correlations for each class.

\( p(p-1)/2 \) which gets big fast.

LDA Estimate

Connection distance

\[ p(x) = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi} \sigma} \exp\left\{ - \frac{(x-\mu)^2}{\sigma^2}\right\} \]

Take out constant and take log:

\[ - \frac{(x-\mu)^2}{\sigma^2} \]

Receiver Operating Characteristic Curves

We have been calling 7s if \( \,\hat{f}(x_1,x_2)>0.5 \).

This cut-off assumes both errors are the same but we have continuum

ROC Curves
